time required: 35 minutes
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Dice @Roma Tomato{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Red Onion{1}; mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Zest and quarter @Lime{1}. Mince @Jalapeño{1}, removing ribs and seeds for less heat. Halve, core, and thinly slice @Long Green Pepper{1} into strips.

In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @Salt{}. Bring to boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, minced onion, a squeeze of lime juice, and as much jalapeño as you like. Season with salt and @Pepper{}. In a separate small bowl, combine @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon}, a squeeze of lime juice, and a pinch of @Chili Powder{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later). Season with salt and pepper. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Heat a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add green pepper and sliced onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{7-9%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Lower heat and add a splash of water if veggies begin to brown too quickly.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #medium bowl{} and cover to keep warm. Wipe out pan.

While veggies cook, pat @Chicken Breast Strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Once veggies are done, heat another drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{1%teaspoon} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken, @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, and remaining chili powder. Cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Stir in @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1} and a splash of water; cook until saucy, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} and lime zest. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between bowls and top with chicken and veggies. Drizzle with crema. Top with @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/4%cup} and pico de gallo. Serve with @Blue Corn Tortilla Chips{1.5%ounce} and remaining lime wedges on the side.